###How to fix the Common Vulnerabilities issue of CVE-2019-0220 in nginx web server and which owasp top 10 web 2021 category this issue belong to ?
To fix the Common Vulnerabilities issue of CVE-2019-0220 in nginx web server, you can follow these steps:

1. Update your nginx web server to the latest version.
2. If you cannot update your nginx web server, you can apply the following patch:
```
http://nginx.org/en/download.html
```
3. If you are using a custom configuration for your nginx web server, you will need to make sure that it does not contain any directives that could be exploited by this vulnerability.

CVE-2019-0220 belongs to the OWASP Top 10 Web 2021 category of "A1 - Injection". This category covers vulnerabilities that allow an attacker to inject malicious code into a web application. Injection vulnerabilities can be exploited to steal data, execute arbitrary commands, or take control of a web application.

Here are some additional tips for preventing injection vulnerabilities:

* Use prepared statements instead of dynamic SQL queries.
* Sanitize all user input before using it in a web application.
* Use a web application firewall (WAF) to help protect against injection attacks.

By following these steps, you can help to protect your nginx web server from the CVE-2019-0220 vulnerability and other injection vulnerabilities.
